Pandas Insight Series 🔥
Basic Attributes (Properties)
df.shape -> Returns a tuple representing the dimensionality (rows, columns)
df.size -> Returns the total number of elements in the DataFrame
df.columns -> Returns the column labels
df.index -> Returns the index (row labels)
df.dtypes -> Returns the data type of each column

Basic Methods (Actions)
df.info() -> Prints a concise summary of the DataFrame including index and dtypes
df.count() -> Counts non-NA cells for each column or row
df.head(n) -> Returns the first n rows (default is 5)
df.tail(n) -> Returns the last n rows (default is 5)
df.describe() -> Generates descriptive statistics for numerical columns

Selection by Label (loc)
df.loc[rows, columns] -> Accesses a group of rows and columns by label(s) or a boolean array

Dropping Data
df.drop(columns=['col_name'], inplace=True) -> Removes specified columns (or rows). If inplace=False, returns a copy.

Handling Missing Data
df.isna() -> Detects missing values, returning a boolean DataFrame
df.dropna() -> Removes rows (or columns) containing missing values
df.fillna(value) -> Replaces missing values with a specified value or method

Data Manipulation
df.sort_values(by='column') -> Sorts the DataFrame by the values of a specific column
df.rename(columns={'old': 'new'}) -> Alters axes labels (renames columns or index)
df.astype(dtype) -> Casts the DataFrame (or Series) to a specified data type
df.drop_duplicates() -> Returns a DataFrame with duplicate rows removed
df.reset_index() -> Resets the index to the default integer index

Grouping and Aggregation
df.groupby('column') -> Groups data based on values in a column for aggregation
df.value_counts() -> Returns a Series containing counts of unique values
df.nunique() -> Counts number of distinct elements in specified axis
df['col'].unique() -> Returns unique values of Series object

Selection by Position (iloc)
df.iloc[row_idx, col_idx] -> Purely integer-location based indexing for selection by position

Merging and Joining
pd.concat([df1, df2]) -> Concatenates pandas objects along a particular axis
df.merge(df2, on='col', how='inner') -> Merges DataFrame objects with a database-style join
pd.merge(df1, df2, left_on='col1', right_on='col2', how='outer') -> Merges DataFrames based on different columns

Function Application
df.apply(func) -> Applies a function along an axis of the DataFrame
df.applymap(func) -> Applies a function to a Dataframe elementwise

String Manipulation (Series)
df['col'].str.contains('pattern') -> Tests if pattern or regex is contained within a string
df['col'].str.lower() -> Converts strings in the Series to lowercase
df['col'].str.replace('old', 'new') -> Replaces occurrences of pattern/regex with some other string

Input/Output
pd.read_csv('path') -> Reads a comma-separated values (csv) file into DataFrame
df.to_csv('path') -> Writes object to a comma-separated values (csv) file